This implementation uses two stacks: `stack_newest_on_top` and `stack_oldest_on_top`. When an item is enqueued, it is pushed onto `stack_newest_on_top`. When an item is dequeued, it is popped from `stack_oldest_on_top`. If `stack_oldest_on_top` is empty, all items are moved from `stack_newest_on_top` to `stack_oldest_on_top` to maintain the correct order.
